:''See also:'' [[Slough]]
==English==
===Pronunciation 1===
slou, /slaʊ/, /<tt>slaU</tt>/<br>
slo͞o, /sluː/, /<tt>slu:</tt>/
====Noun====
'''slough''' (''plural'' '''sloughs''')
#''(UK)'' A muddy or marshy area 
#: ''I lost a boot in the '''slough'''.
#''(Eastern U.S.)'' A type of [[swamp]] or shallow [[lake]] [[system]], typically formed as or by the [[backwater]] of a larger [[waterway]], similar to a [[bayou]] with trees 
#: ''We paddled under a canopy of trees through the '''slough'''.'' 
#''(Western U.S.)'' A secondary channel of a [[river]] [[delta]], usually flushed by the [[tide]]
#: ''The [[w:Sacramento River Delta|Sacramento River Delta]] contains dozens of '''sloughs''' that are often used for water-skiing and fishing.''
#A state of [[depression]]
#: ''John is in a '''slough'''.

===Pronunciation 2===
slŭf, /slʌf/, /<tt>slVf</tt>/
====Noun====
'''slough''' (''plural'' '''sloughs''')

#The skin shed by a [[snake]] or other reptile.
#: ''Here is the '''slough''' of a rattler; we must be careful.''
#Dead skin on a [[sore]] or [[ulcer]].
#: ''This is the '''slough''' that came off of his skin after the burn.''

====Transitive verb====
'''to slough''' ('''sloughing''', '''sloughed''')

#To [[shed]] (skin).
#: ''A week after he was burned, a layer of skin on his arm '''sloughed''' off.''

====Intransitive verb====
'''to slough''' ('''sloughing''', '''sloughed''')

#To be shed (of skin).
#: ''This skin is being '''sloughed'''.''

